# gen70: fallback word-reflecting only for words >= 6 chars.
# Shorter common content words get generic fallback variants instead.
# The word-reflecting path ("Hmm, I don't know about X yet.") was added
# in gen66 to vary the fallback, but it dominated on common 4-5 char
# words giving the impression of cataloguing ignorance. Raising the
# threshold to 6 means the word picker fires only for longer,
# unusual-looking tokens — proper nouns, technical terms, foreign words —
# while common content gets the generic non-understanding variants.
> here is a five word test
< I don't understand that yet.
> more five word test here
< I didn't quite catch that. What would you like to know?
# Words >= 6 chars are still reflected (the existing scherzando case in
# fallback_grounded.chat confirms this path is preserved).
